---
layout: base.njk
active: people
title: People
---
{#
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  This list is driven by content/people/people.json. JSON can't hold comments,
  so the reference shape lives here (it never renders).

  Fields per entry:
    Required:  name   — display text
    Optional:  aka    — nickname; rendered muted as "aka <value>" after the name
               url    — link target; use "" or omit for no link
               links  — array of extra labelled links, each { label, url },
                        rendered as "(label)" after the name

  Reference shape:

      [
        {
          "name": "Carl Sagan",
          "aka": "Sagan",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Sagan",
          "links": [
            { "label": "twitter", "url": "https://twitter.com/..." }
          ]
        }
      ]
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
<h1 class="page-title">People</h1>
<div class="prose">
  <p>
    This list is a collection of the awesome people who have influenced me.
  </p>
</div>
<ul class="people-list">
  {% for p in people | sort(false, false, 'name') %}
  <li>
    <a href="{{ p.url }}">{{ p.name }}</a>{% if p.aka %} <span class="people-aka">aka {{ p.aka }}</span>{% endif %}{% if p.links %}{% for l in p.links %}
    (<a href="{{ l.url }}">{{ l.label }}</a>){% endfor %}{% endif %}
  </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
